		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">17daysolderthannes wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is that metal RF plate necessary for proper operation? or is it like the metal prongs on the 32X that don't really do anything?</div>
<br />Probably not, unless you're actually using RF output. My Sega CD came without the plate, and it looks fine with AV cables (and even better through the 32X--it seems to have a higher-quality video encoder than the Genesis).

		

